---
By: Han Shan
Source:
  ISBN: 1556591403
  Page: 183
  Publisher: Copper Canyon Press
  Title: The Collected Songs of Cold Mountain
  Translator: Red Pine
---
I hiked yesterday to the summit
and peered down a thousand-foot cliff
a tree stood at the edge
the wind bared its two limbs
the rain had stripped it of leaves
the sun had dried it like dust
alas such a once-verdant bloom
is now a pile of ashes
